Unearthed: Ancient Murder Mysteries

Homicide detective Rod Demery and famed scientist Professor Turi King team up to investigate history’s most intriguing murders using modern investigation techniques. Demery visits crime scenes and interviews archaeologist witnesses, while King, best known for leading the DNA verification of Richard III of England, examines the latest forensic evidence. Unearthing a list of suspects for each murder, Demery and King use their extensive experience to predict the killer’s identity. A 6-part series produced by Off the Fence and Curiosity Studios.

Please allow me to continue serving you by voting on 23MAR2024 for me as a Caddo Parish RPEC member, Ballot #60. 

My entire life has been dedicated to public service, whether as a decorated veteran serving honorably at war, as a police officer on the streets, or working in the Caddo Parish District Attorney’s office as a special homicide and conviction integrity investigator. I have been honored to do so.

For many years, I have faithfully served the people of Shreveport and Caddo Parish. I have, quite literally, been at the horrific crime scenes of our children, personally delivering the heart-wrenching news to their families. Alongside the brave men and women of the Shreveport Police Department, we have swiftly brought assailants to justice with integrity.

Now, I wish to continue serving ALL the people of Caddo Parish as a member of the Republican Party executive committee. My bold fairness, decisiveness, and pragmatism, guided by God's direction, will persist in serving our people.

Thank you, and may God bless you.

Rod Demery
And just like that… I’m 58. Thank God for grace and mercy.
